text: Tábor is a municipality in the Czech Republic. It is in the South Bohemian Region. At the 2021 census, 33,360 people lived there. The municipality was started in 1420. The current mayor is Štěpán Pavlík. The municipality is named after Mount Tabor. == Other websites == *Official website Category:Cities in the Czech Republic Category:1420s establishments Category:1420s establishments in Europe Category:South Bohemian Region
